==English==

===Etymology===
Probably from [[po]], abbreviated slang based on French ''[[pot de chambre]]'' ([[chamber pot]]), after the distasteful expression anyone would adopt upon being presented with a full one.  Perhaps similarly from [[pooh]]; perhaps influenced by [[poker-faced]].  Also attested “poor-faced”.

===Adjective===
'''po-faced'''
# Wearing a particularly [[stern]] and [[disapprove|disapproving]] expression; [[humorless]]; [[priggish]].
# [[poker-faced]].